16/01/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Tourism Minister Dan Matei Agathon and wine producers from six regions in the country launched an international advertising campaign, "Romania, Country of Wines", on Wednesday (15 January). 
The programme aims to attract 50,000 new tourists each year. 
Black Sea resorts would offer wine tours to their clients and would recommend popular brands.
In other news, Minister for EU Integration Hildegard Puwak will head a delegation to Brussels next week to finalise negotiations on EU financing under the PHARE programmes for this year. 
The country expects 278.5m euros, allocated primarily to infrastructure projects. 
(Rompres, Mediafax - 16/01/03)
